liars-arrow-the-mindy-project-and-more |title=Spoiler Chat: Scoop on American Horror Story, Pretty Little Liars, Arrow, The Mindy Project and More! |publisher=E! Online |date=July 21, 2015 |accessdate=July 22, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150723073754/http://www.eonline.com/news/678116/spoiler-chat-scoop-on-american-horror-story-pretty-little-liars-arrow-the-mindy-project-and-more |archivedate=July 23, 2015 }}</ref> Franz Drameh was introduced as the new other half of Firestorm in the fourth episode of the second season of ''The Flash''. Crump, Hentschel and James debut in the crossover episodes for the second season of ''The Flash'' and the fourth season of ''Arrow''.<ref name=\"Hentschel\" /><ref name=\"Crump\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/2015/09/24/exclusive-legends-of-tomorrow-casts-peter-francis-james-as-key-p/ |title=EXCLUSIVE: Legends of Tomorrow Casts Peter Francis James As Key Part of Hawkman/Hawkgirl Story |first=Russ |last=Burlingame |publisher=Cominbook.com |date=September 24, 2015 |accessdate=September 24, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161205032204/http://comicbook.com/2015/09/24/exclusive-legends-of-tomorrow-casts-peter-francis-james-as-key-p/ |archivedate=December 5, 2016 }}</ref> In November 2016, the cast of ''Legends of Tomorrow'' appeared on ''The Flash'' and ''Arrow'' as part of the three-part \"[[Invasion! (Arrowverse)|Invasion!]]\" crossover event; the crossover episodes also featured appearances by [[Melissa Benoist]], reprising her role as [[Supergirl (Kara Zor-El)|Kara Danvers / Supergirl]] from the TV series ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]''.\n<!--PLEASE DO NOT ADD CONSTANTINE HERE, AS THAT SHOW HAS NO EFFECT ON LEGENDS OF TOMORROW. IT IS ONLY AFFECTING ARROW AT THIS TIME AND IS NOTED AT THE ARROW PAGE. THANK YOU! -->\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"DeadlineAnnouncement\">{{cite web|url=http:/