-showrunner-1201452806/ |archivedate=June 26, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GustinLegends\">{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/flash-season-2-villain-grant-gustin-legends-tomorrow-guest-star/ |title='The Flash' Star Grant Gustin Teases New Big Bad & 'Legends of Tomorrow' Appearances |last=Vieira |first=Anthony |publisher=Screen Rant |date=June 27, 2015 |accessdate=July 2, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150704002851/http://screenrant.com/flash-season-2-villain-grant-gustin-legends-tomorrow-guest-star/ |archivedate=July 4, 2015 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.cwtv.com/shows/dcs-legends-of-tomorrow}}\n* {{IMDb title|4532368|Legends of Tomorrow}}\n* {{tv.com show|dcs-legends-of-tomorrow|Legends of Tomorrow}}\n\n{{Arrowverse}}\n{{DC Comics TV}}\n{{Greg Berlanti}}\n{{The CW programming}}\n{{Portal bar|Television|United States|Speculative fiction}}\n\n[[Category:Legends of Tomorrow| ]]\n[[Category:2010s American LGBT-related television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American time travel television series]]\n[[Category:2016 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2020s American LGBT-related television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:American action adventure television series]]\n[[Category:American action television series]]\n[[Category:American adventure television series]]\n[[Category:American television spin-offs]]\n[[Category:American time travel television series]]\n[[Category:Bisexuality-related television series]]\n[[Category:Black Canary in other media]]\n[[Category:The CW original programming]]\n[[Category:DC Comics superhero teams]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Flash (comics) in other media]]\n[[Category:Green Arrow in other media]]\n[[Category:Jonah Hex in other media]]\n[[Category:Reincarnation in television]]\n[[Category:Televi