{"title_page": "Aarogya Setu", "text_new": "{{short description|Mobile Application}}\n'''Aarogya Setu''' is a [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] tracking mobile application developed by the [[National Informatics Centre]] that comes under the [[Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology]], [[Government of India]].\n\n[[Image:Aarogya Setu.jpg|right|thumb|200px|The logo of Aarogya Setu app]]\n\n==Overview==\nThe stated purpose of this app is to spread the awareness and to connect essential health services to the people of India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techlinics.com/2020/04/ludo-king-free-download.html|title=Coronavirus pandemic Arogya Setu App Download {{!}} Govt launches COVID-19 tracking app 'Aarogya Setu' for Android, iOS users|website=Techlinics|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />. This app will augment the initiatives of the [[Health department|Department of Health]] to contain the risks of COVID-19, and sharing the best practices and advisories. This is a tracking app which uses smartphone's [[Global Positioning System|GPS]] and [[Bluetooth]] features to track the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] infection. Aarogya Setu app is available for [[Android (operating system)|Android]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=nic.goi.aarogyasetu&hl=en_IN|title=Aarogya Setu \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> and [[iOS]] mobile operating systems<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mygov.in/aarogya-setu-app/|title=Aarogya Setu Mobile App|website=MyGov.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>. Using bluetooth technology, the Aarogya Setu app tries to determine the risk if one has been near a Covid-19 infected person (within six feet of distance) by scanning through a database of known cases across India, and using location information it determines the location one is in belongs to the infected areas based on the data available.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/technology/apps/govt-launches-aarogya-setu-a-coronavirus-tracker-app-all-you-need-to-know-11585821224138.html|title=Govt launches 'Aarogya Setu', a coronavirus tracker app: All you need to know|date=2020-04-02|website=Livemint|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nThis app is an updated version of an earlier app called '''Corona Kavach''' (now discontinued) which was already released by the [[Government of India]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/technology/govt-discontinues-corona-kavach-aarogya-setu-is-now-indias-go-to-covid-19-tracking-app/1919378/|title=Govt discontinues Corona Kavach, Aarogya Setu is now India\u2019s go-to COVID-19 tracking app|date=2020-04-05|website=The Financial Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Aarogya Setu crossed five million downloads within the three days of its launch, making it one of the most popular government apps in India<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gadgets.ndtv.com/apps/news/aarogya-setu-tops-india-charts-on-app-stores-5-million-installs-in-three-days-of-launch-coronavirus-2206060|title=Aarogya Setu App Crosses 5 Million Installs in 3 Days|website=NDTV Gadgets 360|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abplive.com/news/gadgets/coronavirus-india-govts-aarogya-setu-app-crosses-5-million-downloads-in-3-days-1189576|title=Coronavirus India: Govt's 'Aarogya Setu' App Crosses 5 Million Downloads in 3 Days|last=Bureau|first=ABP News|date=2020-04-04|website=news.abplive.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> It is the world's fastest-growing mobile app with more than 50 million installs on the platform, at just 13 days after launching in India on April 2, 2020. <ref>https://www.wionews.com/india-news/aarogya-setu-beats-pokemon-go-record-crosses-50-million-downloads-in-13-days-292605</ref>\n\nAarogya Setu is available currently available in 11 languages<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aarogyasetu.in/|title=Aarogya Setu App|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> (English, Hindi, Telugu, Kannada, Malayalam, Tamil, Punjabi, Bengali, Oriya, Gujarati, and Marathi) and expected to be available in more Indian languages soon. One is asked to provide health and other profiling information after signing into the app. \n\nThe app is also built on a platform that can provide Application Programming Interface<ref name=\":0\" /> ([[Application programming interface|API]]) so that other computer programs, mobile applications and web services can make use of the features and data available of Aarogya setu.\n\n== Features ==\nAarogya Setu has four sections in the new UI, viz, Your Status, Self Assess, COVID-19 Update, and E-pass (which is yet to go active). Your Status tells the risk of getting COVID-19 for the user. Self Assess lets the user know the risk of being infected. COVID-19 Update gives update on the local and national COVID-19 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.jagatgururampalji.org/download-aarogya-setu-app/|title=Aarogya Setu New UI and Features|last=|first=|date=|website=SA News Channel|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Installation Process ==\n\n*First you have to download the App from Google play store or IOS store.\n*After Installing open the App and fill your basic information that requires.\n*# \n*#\n*# \n\n* Soon you will get an OTP, enter it and you are on.\n* Choose your gender from the options.\n* Enter your full name, age, and your profession, as app asked.\n* You'll be asked about your foreign travel history in last 30 days from the App. That's it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/software/how-to-use-aarogya-setu-app-and-find-out-if-you-have-covid-19-symptoms/articleshow/75023152.cms?from=mdr|title=How to use Aarogya Setu app|last=|first=|date=|website=Economics Times|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> <br />\n\n== See also ==\n* [[COVID-19 apps]]\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|https://www.aarogyasetu.in}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:Mobile applications]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n[[Category:Software associated with the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 software]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mobile Application}}\n'''Aarogya Setu''' is a [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] tracking mobile application developed by the [[National Informatics Centre]] that comes under the [[Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology]], [[Government of India]].\n\n[[Image:Aarogya Setu.jpg|right|thumb|200px|The logo of Aarogya Setu app]]\n\n==Overview==\nThe stated purpose of this app is to spread the awareness and to connect essential health services to the people of India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techlinics.com/2020/04/ludo-king-free-download.html|title=Coronavirus pandemic Arogya Setu App Download {{!}} Govt launches COVID-19 tracking app 'Aarogya Setu' for Android, iOS users|website=Techlinics|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />. This app will augment the initiatives of the [[Health department|Department of Health]] to contain the risks of COVID-19, and sharing the best practices and advisories. This is a tracking app which uses smartphone's [[Global Positioning System|GPS]] and [[Bluetooth]] features to track the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] infection. Aarogya Setu app is available for [[Android (operating system)|Android]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=nic.goi.aarogyasetu&hl=en_IN|title=Aarogya Setu \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> and [[iOS]] mobile operating systems<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mygov.in/aarogya-setu-app/|title=Aarogya Setu Mobile App|website=MyGov.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>. Using bluetooth technology, the Aarogya Setu app tries to determine the risk if one has been near a Covid-19 infected person (within six feet of distance) by scanning through a database of known cases across India, and using location information it determines the location one is in belongs to the infected areas based on the data available.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/technology/apps/govt-launches-aarogya-setu-a-coronavirus-tracker-app-all-you-need-to-know-11585821224138.html|title=Govt launches 'Aarogya Setu', a coronavirus tracker app: All you need to know|date=2020-04-02|website=Livemint|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nThis app is an updated version of an earlier app called '''Corona Kavach''' (now discontinued) which was already released by the [[Government of India]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/technology/govt-discontinues-corona-kavach-aarogya-setu-is-now-indias-go-to-covid-19-tracking-app/1919378/|title=Govt discontinues Corona Kavach, Aarogya Setu is now India\u2019s go-to COVID-19 tracking app|date=2020-04-05|website=The Financial Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Aarogya Setu crossed five million downloads within the three days of its launch, making it one of the most popular government apps in India<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gadgets.ndtv.com/apps/news/aarogya-setu-tops-india-charts-on-app-stores-5-million-installs-in-three-days-of-launch-coronavirus-2206060|title=Aarogya Setu App Crosses 5 Million Installs in 3 Days|website=NDTV Gadgets 360|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abplive.com/news/gadgets/coronavirus-india-govts-aarogya-setu-app-crosses-5-million-downloads-in-3-days-1189576|title=Coronavirus India: Govt's 'Aarogya Setu' App Crosses 5 Million Downloads in 3 Days|last=Bureau|first=ABP News|date=2020-04-04|website=news.abplive.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> It is the world's fastest-growing mobile app with more than 50 million users. <ref>https://www.wionews.com/india-news/aarogya-setu-beats-pokemon-go-record-crosses-50-million-downloads-in-13-days-292605</ref>\n\nAarogya Setu is available currently available in 11 languages<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aarogyasetu.in/|title=Aarogya Setu App|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> (English, Hindi, Telugu, Kannada, Malayalam, Tamil, Punjabi, Bengali, Oriya, Gujarati, and Marathi) and expected to be available in more Indian languages soon. One is asked to provide health and other profiling information after signing into the app. \n\nThe app is also built on a platform that can provide Application Programming Interface<ref name=\":0\" /> ([[Application programming interface|API]]) so that other computer programs, mobile applications and web services can make use of the features and data available of Aarogya setu.\n\n== Features ==\nAarogya Setu has four sections in the new UI, viz, Your Status, Self Assess, COVID-19 Update, and E-pass (which is yet to go active). Your Status tells the risk of getting COVID-19 for the user. Self Assess lets the user know the risk of being infected. COVID-19 Update gives update on the local and national COVID-19 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.jagatgururampalji.org/download-aarogya-setu-app/|title=Aarogya Setu New UI and Features|last=|first=|date=|website=SA News Channel|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Installation Process ==\n\n*First you have to download the App from Google play store or IOS store.\n*After Installing open the App and fill your basic information that requires.\n*# \n*#\n*# \n\n* Soon you will get an OTP, enter it and you are on.\n* Choose your gender from the options.\n* Enter your full name, age, and your profession, as app asked.\n* You'll be asked about your foreign travel history in last 30 days from the App. That's it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/software/how-to-use-aarogya-setu-app-and-find-out-if-you-have-covid-19-symptoms/articleshow/75023152.cms?from=mdr|title=How to use Aarogya Setu app|last=|first=|date=|website=Economics Times|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> <br />\n\n== See also ==\n* [[COVID-19 apps]]\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|https://www.aarogyasetu.in}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:Mobile applications]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n[[Category:Software associated with the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 software]]\n", "name_user": "Shashaktbharat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOverview", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aarogya_Setu"}
{"title_page": "Wattpad", "text_new": "{{short description|An online community themed around reading and writing}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name = Wattpad\n| logo = Wattpad logo.png\n| logo_caption = The current, rebranded Wattpad logo (2018\u2013present)\n| screenshot = \n| type = Reading app, [[social networking service]]\n| founder = Allen Lau<br />Ivan Yuen\n| owner = Wattpad Corp.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.wattpad.com/home|website=Wattpad|title=Home|accessdate=2013-11-26}}</ref>\n| alexa = {{Decrease}} 510 (Global, {{as of|2020|4|07|alt=April 7, 2020}})<ref name=\"alexa\">{{cite web|title=wattpad.com Competitive Analysis, Marketing Mix and Traffic|url=https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/wattpad.com|website=www.alexa.com|accessdate=2019-12-07|language=en}}</ref>\n| registration = {{Collapsible list\n | titlestyle = font-weight:normal; text-align:left; background-color:transparent\n | title = Required\n | Required for the majority of the tasks, such as: Editing, creating, or reading stories, view profiles, comment or vote stories and post messages. Registration is also required for unlocking Wattpad Paid Stories with Wattpad Coins ''(since 2018 & 2019)''.\n}}\n| language = English, other 49 available languages. <small>(actual count of: 32 languages)\n| num_users = 80 Million (2019)<ref>[https://betakit.com/wattpad-tracks-80-million-monthly-users-23-percent-growth-since-2018/ Article in ''betakit'']</ref>\n| company_type = [[Private company|Private]]\n| url = {{URL|wattpad.com}}\n| area_served = Worldwide\n| location = [[Toronto, Ontario]], [[Canada]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://foursquare.com/v/wattpad-hq/4ea182a1e3008f7d91ac0f0a|title=Wattpad HQ|website=Foursquare}}</ref>\n| num_employees = 145<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/online-media-startup-wattpad-raises-40-million-from-chinese-internet-giant-tencent/article36638353/Home|title=Tech startup Wattpad raises $40-million from Chinese internet giant Tencentlaccessdate=2017-12-06|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref>\n| native_clients = [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[World Wide Web|Web]].\n| content_license = \n| launch_date = {{start date and age|2006|12}}\n| current_status = Active\n}}{{Primary sources|lead section|date=January 2020}}\n'''Wattpad''' is an Internet community for readers and writers to publish new user-generated stories in different genres, including classics, general fiction, historical fiction, non-fiction, poetry, fan-fiction, spiritual, humor, and teen fiction.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/stories|title=Discover - Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com}}</ref> It aims to create social communities around stories for both amateur and established writers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theliteraryplatform.com/magazine/2012/10/wattpad-building-the-worlds-biggest-reader-and-writer-community/|title=Wattpad: Building the world's biggest reader and writer community - The Literary Platform|publisher=|date=2012-10-18}}</ref>\n\nThe platform claims to have an audience of more than 80 million users, who can directly interact with the writers and share their opinions with fellow readers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2018/1/16/wattpad-raises-51-million-in-funding-from-tencent-bdc-and-other-partners|title=Wattpad Raises $51 Million in Funding from Tencent, BDC and Other Partners|work=Wattpad HQ|access-date=2018-07-16|language=en-US}}</ref> Although available in over 50 languages, 77% of its content is written in English.<ref name=\"wattpad.com\">{{cite web|url=https://blog.wattpad.com/wattpad/2014/04/11/the-international-language-of-storytelling|title=The International Language of Storytelling|publisher=}}</ref> A number of Wattpad users are translating stories to continue to build the platform.<ref name=\"wattpad.com\" />\n\nFrom December 2006 to 2019, the former tagline for the Wattpad website was ''\"Stories you'll love.\"'' As of February/March 2019 during its rebrand to present, it is now ''\"Where stories live\"''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/brand/|title=Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com|access-date=2019-03-11}}</ref>\n\n== History and founder ==\nWattpad originated in 2006, as the result of a collaboration between Allen Lau and Ivan Yuen.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://theliteraryplatform.com/magazine/2012/10/wattpad-building-the-worlds-biggest-reader-and-writer-community/|title=Wattpad: Building the world's biggest reader and writer community - The Literary Platform|newspaper=The Literary Platform|language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-02}}</ref> Their current headquarters, as of 2019, is based in Toronto, Ontario.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\n===Growth and funding===\nIn February 2007, Wattpad announced the addition of over 17,000 [[e-book]]s from [[Project Gutenberg]] making them available to mobile users.<ref name=\"Wattpad\">{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/press|title=Press|website=Wattpad HQ|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref> According to a June 2009 Wattpad press release, the mobile application had been downloaded over 5 million times.<ref name=\"Wattpad\"/> In March 2009, an iPhone version was released. This was followed by the launch on BlackBerry App World in April 2009, Google Android in June 2009 and Apple iPad in April 2010. In December 2015, Windows Phone 8.1 and Windows 10 Mobile Version was released. Currently, Wattpad has more than 65 million users<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/about/|title=About Wattpad|last=Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com}}</ref> who as part of the Wattpad community collectively spend 15 billion minutes each month using Wattpad.<ref name=\"auto\"/> As of 2018 Wattpad there are more than 400 million story uploads on Wattpad.\n[[File:Wattpad logo.svg|alt=An old Wattpad logo dated back from 2006 until 2018. The first letter \"W\" is actually an upside-down letter of M. According to Wattpad Corporation, it was pretty dated and static.|thumb|The old Wattpad logo (2006\u20132018)]]\nAs of January 2018, Wattpad had received almost USD $117.8M in funding from investors.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.wattpad.com/wattpad/2018/1/16/wattpad-raises-51-million-in-funding-from-tencent-bdc-and-other-partners|title=Wattpad Raises $51 Million in Funding from Tencent, BDC and Other Partners|last=|first=|date=|work=VentureBeat|access-date=}}</ref> In 2011, Wattpad announced that it received $3.5M in total funding from its current investors, and from W Media Ventures, Golden Venture Partners, and [[Union Square Ventures]].\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gigaom.com/2011/09/12/union-square-backs-wattpad-to-make-reading-more-social/|title=Union Square backs Wattpad to make reading more social|last=Ingram|first=Mathew|date=2011-09-12}}</ref> Then in June 2012, Wattpad raised $17.3M from a group of venture funds led by Khosla Ventures.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gigaom.com/2012/06/06/wattpad-raises-17-million-to-become-the-youtube-of-writing/|title=Wattpad raises $17 million to become the YouTube of writing|first=Mathew|last=Ingram|publisher=|date=2012-06-06}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2014, Wattpad announced $46M in Series C funding led by OMERS ventures.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2014/04/08/wattpad-funding/|title=Wattpad Raises $46 Million to Build a Global Literary Community|date=8 April 2014|work=Mashable}}</ref> In January 2018, Wattpad announced USD $51M in funding from [[Tencent|Tencent Holdings Limited]], BDC, Globe Telecom's Kickstart Ventures, Peterson Group, Canso, and existing investor Raine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-01-17/tencent-leads-51-million-investment-in-canadian-startup-wattpad|title=Tencent Leads $51 Million Investment in Canadian Startup Wattpad|date=2018-01-17|work=Bloomberg.com|access-date=2018-02-20|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards ===\nIn December 2011, Toronto-based Wattpad was selected as the hottest Digital Media company in the country at the Canadian Innovation Exchange.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.itbusiness.ca/news/wave-accounting-and-wattpad-win-peoples-choice-awards-at-cix/16717|title=Wave Accounting and Wattpad win people's choice awards at CIX|first=Brian|last=Jackson|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref> In the same year, co-founder and CEO Ivan Yuen was also recognized as a top Canadian entrepreneur at the Impact Infused Awards, sponsored by [[Deloitte]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.deloitte.com/view/en_CA/ca/pressroom/ca-pressreleases-en/58b44ca2284c3310VgnVCM3000001c56f00aRCRD.htm|title=Impact and Deloitte Press Release|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Wattpad in the Philippines===\n{{More citations needed section|date=January 2020}}\nIn March 2014, Wattpad signed a contract with Pop Fiction, an imprint of [[Summit Media]], to print Filipino Wattpad stories in the [[Philippines]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.summitmedia.com.ph/news/summit-media-wattpad-partnership/|title=Summit Media and Wattpad ink partnership to publish more works by online writers in the Philippines|date=March 24, 2014|publisher=[[Summit Media]]|access-date=September 17, 2014}}</ref> Other publishers from the Philippines also publish stories from Wattpad.\n\nSince then, some Wattpad stories have also been adapted into [[Philippine drama|teleseries]]. Filipino television network [[The 5 Network|TV5]], in partnership with Wattpad and Life is Beautiful Publishing Company launched ''Wattpad Presents'', a series of Wattpad stories turned into TV dramas.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} Wattpad stories aired on the show are usually those that were published by LIB Publishing.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n\n[[ABS-CBN]] also made several adaptation of Wattpad stories such as \"My App Boyfie\" by Noreen Capili (noringai), starring [[James Reid (entertainer)|James Reid]] and [[Nadine Lustre]], and the coming-of-age series [[Bagito]] starring [[Nash Aguas]], [[Alexa Ilacad]] and [[Ella Cruz]].{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} Pop Fiction's best-selling book, \"She's Dating the Gangster\", written by Bianca Bernardino (SGWannaB) as a Wattpad original, became the first Wattpad story adapted into a full-length motion picture starring [[Kathryn Bernardo]] and [[Daniel Padilla]].\" The movie adaptation was produced by ABS-CBN's film production arm, Star Cinema.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} [[Liza Soberano]] and [[Enrique Gil]] also starred on the film \"[[Just the Way You Are (2015 film)|Just The Way You Are]]\", based on the Wattpad story \"The Bet\" by Ilurvbooks.\" \"Chasing Red\" was published by a Wattpad user which got more than 200 million views.{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n\n=== Wattpad After Dark ===\nIn February 2015, Wattpad launched a second standalone app called \"After Dark\".<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://happyeverafter.usatoday.com/2015/02/26/wattpad-after-dark-steamy-romance-app/|title = Wattpad Launches After Dark app for Steamy Romance|date = |accessdate = |website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> The app focuses specifically on the romance genre and is intended for adult readers.\n\n===Tap===\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Tap Original - The Babysitter Part III.jpg|thumb|right|Cover artwork for one of Tap's biggest Original Series, ''The Babysitter''.{{deletable image-caption|Sunday, 17 June 2018|PROD}}]] -->\nOn February 21, 2017, Wattpad launched a chat stories app called ''Tap''.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://techcrunch.com/2017/02/22/wattpad-debuts-tap-an-app-for-reading-chat-style-short-stories/|title = Wattpad debuts Tap, an app for reading chat-style short stories|date = February 22, 2017|accessdate = June 13, 2017|website =TechCrunch |publisher = |last =Perez |first =Sarah }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = https://the-digital-reader.com/2017/02/22/wattpad-launches-chat-style-reading-app-tap/|title = Wattpad Launches Chat-Style Reading App Tap|date = February 22, 2017|accessdate = June 13, 2017|website =The Digital Reader |publisher = |last =Hoffelder |first =Nate }}</ref> ''Tap'' offers stories in the form of text messages as if reading a private conversation on someone else's phone. The app was an early success, with over 240 million taps in the first few weeks after the launch.<ref>{{Cite news|url = https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/books-and-media/wattpad-taps-into-a-new-genre/article34335985/|title = Wattpad taps into a new genre|date = March 17, 2017|accessdate = June 13, 2017|website =The Globe and Mail |publisher =|last =Dingman |first =Shane }}</ref> On July 28, 2017, Tap launched 'Tap Originals', a series of original stories produced by its top-tier writers every single week, with some of those series working on an episode-by-episode basis.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://techcrunch.com/2017/07/28/wattpad-takes-chat-fiction-beyond-text-with-launch-of-tap-originals/|title = Wattpad takes 'chat fiction' beyond text with launch of Tap Originals|date = July 28, 2017|access-date = December 1, 2017|website =Tech Crunch |publisher = |last =Perez |first =Sarah }}</ref> Some of Tap's most successful original series include ''HIDE'', ''The Babysitter'' and ''Charlie, Charlie''.\n\n=== Wattpad Next Beta ===<!-- This information was retrieved from these references. You can edit them if you spot wrong grammars or spellings, or with other reasons, but do not delete them, unless with a valid reason in your summary, otherwise, I will undo your deletion of this sentence. -->\n\nOn November 13, 2018, Wattpad Next Beta was launched<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nextbeta.wattpad.com/|title=Wattpad Next|website=Wattpad Next|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-09}}</ref> to selected countries<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2018/11/13/wattpad-announces-us-launch-for-wattpad-next-beta-program-adding-exclusive-paid-content-to-the-platform|title=Wattpad Announces US Launch for Wattpad Next (Beta) Program, Adding Exclusive Paid Content to the Platform|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-09}}</ref> for early testing such as [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[Mexico]], [[United Kingdom]], and the [[Philippines]]. The launch of the Next Beta has over 50 exclusively selected stories to be paid with WattPad Coins, that can be earned by having your reader spend Wattpad Coins to show them support or by purchasing them with real-world currency to unlock participating Next Beta stories. This has been launched to create a way for writers to earn money through their work and to provide support for readers. WattPad has planned a fast-follow launch for Wattpad Next (Beta) in [[Spanish language|Spanish-speaking regions]] and to expand the program, and was available in [[Latin America]] and [[Spain]], beginning May 27, 2019 and later worldwide on July 11th the same year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/714856760-news-updates-april-3rd-2019-thank-you-next|title=News & Updates - April 3rd, 2019 - Thank you, Next. Introducing Paid Stories. - Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref>\n\nIn an article<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://support.wattpad.com/hc/en-us/articles/360022692911-Introducing-Paid-Stories|title=Introducing Paid Stories|website=Help Center|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref> posted on September 17, 2019, almost a month before the 1st year since the launch of Next Beta, The Wattpad Team has announced the ending of the Next Beta program after results from the program showed that \"Wattpadders are ready for a program that funds writers.\". By that time, it was renamed as \"Paid Stories\".\n\nThere are also paid books which requires an reader to pay money to read further chapters in the book. Usually the paid books are in better quality than the ones that are not paid.\n\n== Usage ==\n===Statistics=== \nAs of August 2019:\n* 85% of its traffic and usage comes from mobile devices,<ref name=\"gigaom.com\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/wattpad-funding-tencent-tv-film-entertainment-1202666935/|title=Wattpad Banks $51 Million From Tencent, Other Investors to Fund Entertainment Projects|author=Mathew Ingram|date=2018-01-17|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* the site has 80 million monthly users,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://betakit.com/wattpad-tracks-80-million-monthly-users-23-percent-growth-since-2018/|title=Wattpad tracks 80 million monthly users, 23 percent increase since 2018|date=2019-08-15|website=BetaKit|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n* there are over 665 million story uploads in total,<ref name=\"Wattpad\"/>\n* 70% of users are female. 80% of whom are millennials or Gen Z.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rao |first1=Sonia |title=How 'The Kissing Booth' went from a teenager's passion project to a Netflix sensation |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/how-the-kissing-booth-went-from-a-teenagers-passion-project-to-a-netflix-sensation/2018/07/13/712c0072-84fe-11e8-9e80-403a221946a7_story.html?noredirect=on |website=Washington Post |publisher=WP Company LLC |accessdate=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== New authors and teens ===\nThe most frequently voted stories appear on the \"What's Hot List\". According to the profiles visible on the site, many of these authors are teenagers.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}{{Primary source inline|date=January 2020}}\n\nWattpad section also has a Featured Story list, which promotes content reviewed and approved by staff and an editorial review board. Many of these featured stories are written by self-published and professional writers from different genres. Famous authors like [[Margaret Atwood]], [[Paulo Coelho]] and [[R L Stine]] have also joined wattpad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/publishedwriters/|title=Promote and Market your Book on Wattpad for Published Authors|last=Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com}}</ref> Wattpad also encourages the writers to interact with their audience and promote their stories across social media websites like Twitter, Facebook, YouTube and Instagram.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://support.wattpad.com/hc/en-us|title=Help Center|website=support.wattpad.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Contests ===\nWattpad hosts a number of writing contests each year, including the annual Watty Awards, the largest writing competition in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/go/writing-contests/|title=Writing Contests on Wattpad|website=Wattpad}}</ref> In 2011, The Watty Awards introduced three entry levels (Popular, On The Rise, and Undiscovered) to allow greater chances of winning for every type of writer. [[Competition|Contests]] are open to anyone who has a Wattpad account.\n\nDuring the summer of 2012, Wattpad in collaboration with [[Margaret Atwood]], Canadian poet/novelist/literary critic, held the \"Wattys\": the first major poetry contest offering a chance to poets on Wattpad to compete against each other in one of two categories, either as an \"Enthusiast\" or a \"Competitor\". It has been going ever since, and now the contest is open to books of all genres.\n\n=== Publishing ===\nWattpad has formed ties with publishing houses to try to help Wattpad authors to receive compensation for their works. A new branch, Wattpad Studios, was developed to connect popular writers to both the publishing and film industries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/04/26/wattpad-studios/|title=Wattpad sets its sights on brands, publishers and Hollywood with Wattpad Studios|last=Ha|first=Anthony|website=TechCrunch|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref> Wattpad has, in the past, teamed up with publishing groups such as [[Sourcebooks]] to help Wattpad authors receive book deals, and get their work into hard copies.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/childrens/childrens-book-news/article/58997-sourcebooks-wattpad-team-up-to-launch-ya-authors.html|title=Sourcebooks, Wattpad Team Up To Launch YA Authors|newspaper=PublishersWeekly.com|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref> More traditional publishing houses such as [[Random House]] and [[HarperCollins]] have approached popular Wattpad writers to negotiate publishing deals, allowing the website to serve as a springboard into the more traditional publishing industry.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/what-wattpad-youtube-stories-transforming-book-publishing-1710151|title=What Is Wattpad? The 'YouTube For Stories' Is Transforming Book Publishing|date=2014-10-23|newspaper=International Business Times|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref>\n\nAuthor [[Anna Todd]], whose work ''After'' has received over a billion reads on the site, was given a publishing deal with [[Simon & Schuster]] to turn her online work into a multiple-book published saga. A film version starring Josephine Langford, Hero Fiennes Tiffin, Selma Blair, Jennifer Beals, Peter Gallagher, and Shane Paul McGhie was released by Aviron Pictures on April 12, 2019.\n\n==== Wattpad Books ====\nOn January 24, 2019, Wattpad launched publishing division Wattpad Books led by Wattpad Studios' Publishing Deputy Manager Ashleigh Gardner, with operations managed by Wattpad Studios' Publishing Director Deanna McFadden.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/1/23/wattpad-launches-wattpad-books-a-new-publishing-division-to-bring-diverse-data-backed-stories-to-book-lovers-everywhere|title=Wattpad Launches Wattpad Books, a New Publishing Division to Bring Diverse, Data-Backed Stories to Book-Lovers Everywhere|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref> According to CEO Allen Lau, this project was in an effort to take the \"guesswork\" out of publishing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.utoronto.ca/news/wattpad-founded-u-t-alumni-launches-publishing-division-new-york-times|title=Wattpad, founded by U of T alumni, launches publishing division: New York Times|website=University of Toronto News|language=en|access-date=2019-03-24}}</ref>\n\nWattpad Books acquisitions uses a mix of their Story DNA Machine Learning technology (algorithms) learning with human editors.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/1/24/18195753/wattpad-books-launching-publishing-imprint-self|title=Wattpad is launching a publishing imprint called Wattpad Books|last=Liptak|first=Andrew|date=2019-01-24|website=The Verge|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref> This human-and-digital acquisitions team look to Wattpad's large and existing digital library (over half a billion titles) in order to select notable material for publication.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/lilyrugo/2019/01/30/wattpads-new-book-publishing-branch-uses-machine-deep-learning-to-find-stories/|title=Wattpad's New Book Publishing Branch Uses Machine Deep Learning To Find Stories|last=Rugo|first=Lily|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-03-24}}</ref> According to Wattpad Books leader Ashleigh Gardner, this is in an effort to combat bias inherent in human editors.<ref name=\":2\" /> Gardner says that this technology analyzes the data behind each title, looking at story structure and word use in addition to levels of reader engagement per title.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebookseller.com/futurebook/algorithms-trends-and-partnerships-inside-story-wattpad-books-942486|title=Algorithms, trends and partnerships: the inside story of Wattpad books|last=Flatt|first=Molly|date=February 4, 2019|website=The Bookseller|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref> This data is then compared to analyses of other books on Wattpad and in the public domain.<ref name=\":0\" /> Once all the data has been collected and engagement has been looked at, human staffers read the titles and create their list.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nAll published titles are an amalgamation of international hits and notable but known material from their digital library.<ref name=\":1\" /> These titles are distributed by Macmillan in the United States of America, Raincoast Books in Canada, and Penguin Random House in India and the United Kingdom, with their Fall 2019 list available in leading North American retailers.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/7/8/penguin-random-house-india-partners-with-wattpad-to-showcase-exclusive-content-and-innovative-promotions|title=Penguin Random House India Partners with Wattpad to Showcase Exclusive Content and Innovative Promotions|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/8/8/penguin-random-house-uk-collaborates-with-wattpad-books-to-bring-global-wattpad-hits-to-readers-in-the-uk|title=Penguin Random House UK collaborates with Wattpad Books to bring global Wattpad hits to readers in the UK|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref> Outside North America, Gardner has sold the rights to Hachette (France) for Deanna Cameron\u2019s ''What Happened Last Night.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://publishingperspectives.com/2019/01/wattpad-books-new-publishing-division-opened-canada/|title=Wattpad Launches a Book Publishing Division Called Wattpad Books|date=2019-01-24|website=Publishing Perspectives|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref> Additionally, Lauren Palphreyman's rights to ''Cupid's Match'' have been sold in French (Hachette) and German (S. Fischer Verlgage).<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://social.techcrunch.com/2019/01/24/online-storytelling-community-wattpad-launches-its-own-publishing-arm-wattpad-books/|title=Online storytelling community Wattpad launches its own publishing arm, Wattpad Books|website=TechCrunch|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref>\n\nWattpad's first list consists of six young adult novels.<ref name=\":3\" /> ''The QB Bad Boy & Me'' by Tay Marley (28.8 million reads) will be their lead title and was slated for release on August 13, 2019.<ref name=\":3\" /> The remaining five books will be released between September and October 2019 and include: ''Trapeze'' by Leigh Ansell (2.5 million reads), ''What Happened That Night'' by Deanna Cameron (over 1 million reads), ''Saving Everest'' by Sky Reads (17.2 million reads), ''Cupid's Match'' by Lauren Palphreyman (46.4 million reads), and ''I'm a Gay Wizard'' by V.S. Santoni (404,000 reads).<ref name=\":3\" /> Wattpad hopes to publish 18 titles in their 2020 list.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nBesides Wattpad Books, Wattpad announced partnership with Anvil Publishing, Inc., one of Philippines' leading publishers, to create Bliss Books, a YA imprint with Filipino Young Adult and romance fanatics as their target market.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/4/15/anvil-publishing-and-wattpad-team-up-for-bliss-books-a-new-ya-imprint-for-the-philippines|title=Anvil Publishing and Wattpad Team Up for Bliss Books, a New YA Imprint for the Philippines|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref>\n\n=== Entertainment ===\n[[Netflix]] film [[The Kissing Booth]] was written in 2011 by author Beth Reekles. It originated as a story on Wattpad where it won a Watty Award for \"Most Popular Teen Fiction\" in Wattpad's annual writing contest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2013/04/beth-reekles-kissing-booth/316454/|title=Meet the 17-Year-Old Who's Already Got a Three-Book Deal with Random House|first=Jen|last=Doll|date=Apr 9, 2013|website=The Atlantic|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref> By 2012 it had amassed over 19 million reads on Wattpad and, in 2013, was published by [[Penguin Random House]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://social.techcrunch.com/2018/06/14/netflixs-latest-hit-the-kissing-booth-is-a-wattpad-success-story/|title=Netflix's latest hit 'The Kissing Booth' is a Wattpad success story|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref> In an interview with [[Forbes]], Reekles explains what drew her to Wattpad: \"I loved the feeling of community on the site, and when I began to share, I liked the anonymity of it because I was so self-conscious about my writing and hadn't shared it with anyone before.\"<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/adamrowe1/2018/06/26/why-beth-reekles-is-the-wattpad-success-story-behind-netflix-hit-the-kissing-booth/|title=Why Beth Reekles Is The Wattpad Success Story Behind Netflix Hit 'The Kissing Booth'|first=Adam|last=Rowe|website=Forbes|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\nSince [[The Kissing Booth]] premiered on [[Netflix]] on May 11, 2018, [[Ted Sarandos]] called it \"one of the most-watched movies in the country, and maybe in the world\".<ref name=\"auto1\"/> The Kissing Booth was the fourth most-popular movie in [[IMDb]]'s popularity rankings in June 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/netflix-says-the-kissing-booth-is-one-of-the-most-watched-movies-in-the-country-2018-6|title=Netflix says its teen romcom 'The Kissing Booth' is 'one of the most-watched movies in the country'|first=Travis|last=Clark|website=Business Insider|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019|date=2018-06-12}}</ref> Wattpad has also inked deals with Asian distribution partners,such as pan-Asian streaming platform [[Iflix]] to co-produce dozens of original movies based on Wattpad stories out of Indonesia,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/wattpad-strikes-original-content-partnership-with-asian-digital-platform-iflix-1202445743/|title=Wattpad Strikes Original Content Partnership With Asian Digital Platform Iflix|last=|first=|date=2018-08-15|website=Deadline|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and Singapore's [[Mediacorp]], to bring Wattpad stories to Mediacorp's FTA channels such as [[Channel 5 (Singapore)|Channel 5]] (with exception of [[CNA (news channel)|CNA]]) and its streaming service Toggle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/4/23/wattpad-and-mediacorp-partner-to-bring-singapore-stories-from-written-word-to-national-screens|title=Wattpad and Mediacorp partner to bring Singapore stories from written word to national screens|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref>\n\nWattpad, with [[AwesomenessTV]],  produces [[Hulu]]'s popular [[Light as a Feather (TV series)|Light as a Feather]].\n\n== Effects on writers ==\nOnline writing communities like Wattpad help adolescent writers learn and grow their craft from constructive feedback and criticism, according to a recent study.<ref name=\":02\">{{Cite journal|last=Birch|first=Heather|date=2016|title=Feedback in Online Writing Forums: Effects on Adolescent Writers|url=https://scholarworks.wmich.edu/wte/vol5/iss1/5/|journal=Teaching/Writing: The Journal of Writing Teacher Education|volume=5|pages=Article 5|via=}}</ref> Composed of students and their experiences on online writing platforms, the study aims to show how constructive criticism affects their writing process. Most participants prefer serious feedback over subtle critiquing, based on the results.<ref name=\":02\" />\n\nWattpad as well as similar online writing communities help young authors build and construct their self perception as writers, as well as establishes an audience and interact with readers.<ref name=\":12\">{{Cite journal|last=Ramdarshan Bold|first=Melanie|date=2016|title=The Return of the Social Author: Negotiating Authority and Influence on Wattpad|journal=Convergence|volume=|pages=|doi=10.1177/1354856516654459}}</ref> It acts as a gateway into the publishing realm and offers hands-on experience with digital writing. This type of experience helps writers develop personal authorship.<ref name=\":12\" />\n\nWattpad offers unique features that other writing platforms do not, like the interactive margin commenting. Readers can add comments and feedback by individual lines and paragraphs as they are reading rather than after the chapter or story is finished.<ref name=\":22\">{{Cite journal|last=Rebora|first=Simone|date=2018|title=A New Research Programme for Reading Research: Analysing Comments in the Margins on Wattpad|url=https://digitcult.lim.di.unimi.it/index.php/dc/article/view/67|journal=DigitCult - Scientific Journal on Digital Cultures|volume=3|pages=19\u201336|via=}}</ref> These comment sections are available to all users and readers for reacting to the chapter, offering constructive feedback, or just for personal input, allowing readers to see what others are thinking and writers to see how readers are responding.<ref name=\":22\" />\n\n== Copyright issues ==\nEarly in its history, some of the large volumes of user-uploaded material hosted on Wattpad was [[copyright infringement|copyrighted material]] created by authors who did not grant republication rights. In May 2009, an article in 'The New York Times' noted, \"''Sites like [[Scribd]] and Wattpad, which invite users to upload documents like college theses and self-published novels, have been the target of industry grumbling in recent weeks, as illegal reproductions of popular titles have turned up on them''\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/05/12/technology/internet/12digital.html|title=With E-Readers Comes Wider Piracy of Books|last=Rich|first=Motoko|date=2009-05-11|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\nThe Wattpad website notes, \"We do not welcome upload of material that violate its copyright terms,\" but also states \"it is simply not possible to screen and verify all posted content.\"<ref name=\"writerprogram\">{{citation|url=http://www.wattpad.com/writerprogram|title=Wattpad \u2013 Writer Program}}.</ref> In response to industry criticism, in April 2009 (before the publication of the ''New York Times'' article that named Wattpad as a vehicle for user-generated e-book infringement) Wattpad announced an \"Authors In Charge\" program, designed to allow authors or their representatives to identify and directly remove infringing content from the site, but this program is designed specifically for \"authors with published books for sale.\"<ref name=writerprogram/> Authors may begin their stories on Wattpad and then chose to publish their work. In most cases, the work on Wattpad is only a sample to insure funds going to them in regards to their writing.\n\n== Competitors and similar sites==\n[[Bookmate]] and the long-established and popular sites [[FanFiction.Net]] and [[Fiction Press]] (a spin-off site for original fiction) also serve as hubs for online prose. An alternative site which is free and open source is [[Archive of Our Own]], or AO3.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gizmodo.com/how-to-find-the-best-fanfiction-on-the-internet-1723984681|title=How To Find The Best Fanfiction On the Internet|last=Hale-Stern|first=Kaila|work=Gizmodo|access-date=2017-12-06|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{E-book digital distribution platforms}}\n{{Self-publishing}}\n\n[[Category:Wattpad]]\n[[Category:Canadian publishers (people)]]\n[[Category:E-book suppliers]]\n[[Category:Electronic paper technology]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) software]]\n[[Category:BlackBerry software]]\n[[Category:IOS software]]\n[[Category:E-book sources]]\n[[Category:Online publishing companies]]\n[[Category:Self-publishing companies]]\n[[Category:Universal Windows Platform apps]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|An online community themed around reading and writing}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name = Wattpad\n| logo = Wattpad logo.png\n| logo_caption = The current, rebranded Wattpad logo (2018\u2013present)\n| screenshot = \n| type = Reading app, [[social networking service]]\n| founder = Allen Lau<br />Ivan Yuen\n| owner = Wattpad Corp.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.wattpad.com/home|website=Wattpad|title=Home|accessdate=2013-11-26}}</ref>\n| alexa = {{Decrease}} 510 (Global, {{as of|2020|4|07|alt=April 7, 2020}})<ref name=\"alexa\">{{cite web|title=wattpad.com Competitive Analysis, Marketing Mix and Traffic|url=https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/wattpad.com|website=www.alexa.com|accessdate=2019-12-07|language=en}}</ref>\n| registration = {{Collapsible list\n | titlestyle = font-weight:normal; text-align:left; background-color:transparent\n | title = Required\n | Required for the majority of the tasks, such as: Editing, creating, or reading stories, view profiles, comment or vote stories and post messages. Registration is also required for unlocking Wattpad Paid Stories with Wattpad Coins ''(since 2018 & 2019)''.\n}}\n| language = English, other 49 available languages. <small>(actual count of: 32 languages)\n| num_users = 80 Million (2019)<ref>[https://betakit.com/wattpad-tracks-80-million-monthly-users-23-percent-growth-since-2018/ Article in ''betakit'']</ref>\n| company_type = [[Private company|Private]]\n| url = {{URL|wattpad.com}}\n| area_served = Worldwide\n| location = [[Toronto, Ontario]], [[Canada]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://foursquare.com/v/wattpad-hq/4ea182a1e3008f7d91ac0f0a|title=Wattpad HQ|website=Foursquare}}</ref>\n| num_employees = 145<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/online-media-startup-wattpad-raises-40-million-from-chinese-internet-giant-tencent/article36638353/Home|title=Tech startup Wattpad raises $40-million from Chinese internet giant Tencentlaccessdate=2017-12-06|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref>\n| native_clients = [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[World Wide Web|Web]].\n| content_license = \n| launch_date = {{start date and age|2006|12}}\n| current_status = Active\n}}{{Primary sources|lead section|date=January 2020}}\n'''Wattpad''' is an Internet community for readers and writers to publish new user-generated stories in different genres, including classics, general fiction, historical fiction, non-fiction, poetry, fan-fiction, spiritual, humor, and teen fiction.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/stories|title=Discover - Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com}}</ref> It aims to create social communities around stories for both amateur and established writers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theliteraryplatform.com/magazine/2012/10/wattpad-building-the-worlds-biggest-reader-and-writer-community/|title=Wattpad: Building the world's biggest reader and writer community - The Literary Platform|publisher=|date=2012-10-18}}</ref>\n\nThe platform claims to have an audience of more than 80 million users, who can directly interact with the writers and share their opinions with fellow readers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2018/1/16/wattpad-raises-51-million-in-funding-from-tencent-bdc-and-other-partners|title=Wattpad Raises $51 Million in Funding from Tencent, BDC and Other Partners|work=Wattpad HQ|access-date=2018-07-16|language=en-US}}</ref> Although available in over 50 languages, 77% of its content is written in English.<ref name=\"wattpad.com\">{{cite web|url=https://blog.wattpad.com/wattpad/2014/04/11/the-international-language-of-storytelling|title=The International Language of Storytelling|publisher=}}</ref> A number of Wattpad users are translating stories to continue to build the platform.<ref name=\"wattpad.com\" />\n\nFrom December 2006 to 2019, the former tagline for the Wattpad website was ''\"Stories you'll love.\"'' As of February/March 2019 during its rebrand to present, it is now ''\"Where stories live\"''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/brand/|title=Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com|access-date=2019-03-11}}</ref>\n\n== History and founder ==\nWattpad originated in 2006, as the result of a collaboration between Allen Lau and Ivan Yuen.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://theliteraryplatform.com/magazine/2012/10/wattpad-building-the-worlds-biggest-reader-and-writer-community/|title=Wattpad: Building the world's biggest reader and writer community - The Literary Platform|newspaper=The Literary Platform|language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-02}}</ref> Their current headquarters, as of 2019, is based in Toronto, Ontario.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\n===Growth and funding===\nIn February 2007, Wattpad announced the addition of over 17,000 [[e-book]]s from [[Project Gutenberg]] making them available to mobile users.<ref name=\"Wattpad\">{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/press|title=Press|website=Wattpad HQ|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref> According to a June 2009 Wattpad press release, the mobile application had been downloaded over 5 million times.<ref name=\"Wattpad\"/> In March 2009, an iPhone version was released. This was followed by the launch on BlackBerry App World in April 2009, Google Android in June 2009 and Apple iPad in April 2010. In December 2015, Windows Phone 8.1 and Windows 10 Mobile Version was released. Currently, Wattpad has more than 65 million users<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/about/|title=About Wattpad|last=Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com}}</ref> who as part of the Wattpad community collectively spend 15 billion minutes each month using Wattpad.<ref name=\"auto\"/> As of 2018 Wattpad there are more than 400 million story uploads on Wattpad.\n[[File:Wattpad logo.svg|alt=An old Wattpad logo dated back from 2006 until 2018. The first letter \"W\" is actually an upside-down letter of M. According to Wattpad Corporation, it was pretty dated and static.|thumb|The old Wattpad logo (2006\u20132018)]]\nAs of January 2018, Wattpad had received almost USD $117.8M in funding from investors.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.wattpad.com/wattpad/2018/1/16/wattpad-raises-51-million-in-funding-from-tencent-bdc-and-other-partners|title=Wattpad Raises $51 Million in Funding from Tencent, BDC and Other Partners|last=|first=|date=|work=VentureBeat|access-date=}}</ref> In 2011, Wattpad announced that it received $3.5M in total funding from its current investors, and from W Media Ventures, Golden Venture Partners, and [[Union Square Ventures]].\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gigaom.com/2011/09/12/union-square-backs-wattpad-to-make-reading-more-social/|title=Union Square backs Wattpad to make reading more social|last=Ingram|first=Mathew|date=2011-09-12}}</ref> Then in June 2012, Wattpad raised $17.3M from a group of venture funds led by Khosla Ventures.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gigaom.com/2012/06/06/wattpad-raises-17-million-to-become-the-youtube-of-writing/|title=Wattpad raises $17 million to become the YouTube of writing|first=Mathew|last=Ingram|publisher=|date=2012-06-06}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2014, Wattpad announced $46M in Series C funding led by OMERS ventures.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2014/04/08/wattpad-funding/|title=Wattpad Raises $46 Million to Build a Global Literary Community|date=8 April 2014|work=Mashable}}</ref> In January 2018, Wattpad announced USD $51M in funding from [[Tencent|Tencent Holdings Limited]], BDC, Globe Telecom's Kickstart Ventures, Peterson Group, Canso, and existing investor Raine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-01-17/tencent-leads-51-million-investment-in-canadian-startup-wattpad|title=Tencent Leads $51 Million Investment in Canadian Startup Wattpad|date=2018-01-17|work=Bloomberg.com|access-date=2018-02-20|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards ===\nIn December 2011, Toronto-based Wattpad was selected as the hottest Digital Media company in the country at the Canadian Innovation Exchange.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.itbusiness.ca/news/wave-accounting-and-wattpad-win-peoples-choice-awards-at-cix/16717|title=Wave Accounting and Wattpad win people's choice awards at CIX|first=Brian|last=Jackson|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref> In the same year, co-founder and CEO Ivan Yuen was also recognized as a top Canadian entrepreneur at the Impact Infused Awards, sponsored by [[Deloitte]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.deloitte.com/view/en_CA/ca/pressroom/ca-pressreleases-en/58b44ca2284c3310VgnVCM3000001c56f00aRCRD.htm|title=Impact and Deloitte Press Release|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Wattpad in the Philippines===\n{{More citations needed section|date=January 2020}}\nIn March 2014, Wattpad signed a contract with Pop Fiction, an imprint of [[Summit Media]], to print Filipino Wattpad stories in the [[Philippines]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.summitmedia.com.ph/news/summit-media-wattpad-partnership/|title=Summit Media and Wattpad ink partnership to publish more works by online writers in the Philippines|date=March 24, 2014|publisher=[[Summit Media]]|access-date=September 17, 2014}}</ref> Other publishers from the Philippines also publish stories from Wattpad.\n\nSince then, some Wattpad stories have also been adapted into [[Philippine drama|teleseries]]. Filipino television network [[The 5 Network|TV5]], in partnership with Wattpad and Life is Beautiful Publishing Company launched ''Wattpad Presents'', a series of Wattpad stories turned into TV dramas.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} Wattpad stories aired on the show are usually those that were published by LIB Publishing.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n\n[[ABS-CBN]] also made several adaptation of Wattpad stories such as \"My App Boyfie\" by Noreen Capili (noringai), starring [[James Reid (entertainer)|James Reid]] and [[Nadine Lustre]], and the coming-of-age series [[Bagito]] starring [[Nash Aguas]], [[Alexa Ilacad]] and [[Ella Cruz]].{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} Pop Fiction's best-selling book, \"She's Dating the Gangster\", written by Bianca Bernardino (SGWannaB) as a Wattpad original, became the first Wattpad story adapted into a full-length motion picture starring [[Kathryn Bernardo]] and [[Daniel Padilla]].\" The movie adaptation was produced by ABS-CBN's film production arm, Star Cinema.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} [[Liza Soberano]] and [[Enrique Gil]] also starred on the film \"[[Just the Way You Are (2015 film)|Just The Way You Are]]\", based on the Wattpad story \"The Bet\" by Ilurvbooks.\" \"Chasing Red\" was published by a Wattpad user which got more than 200 million views.{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n\n=== Wattpad After Dark ===\nIn February 2015, Wattpad launched a second standalone app called \"After Dark\".<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://happyeverafter.usatoday.com/2015/02/26/wattpad-after-dark-steamy-romance-app/|title = Wattpad Launches After Dark app for Steamy Romance|date = |accessdate = |website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> The app focuses specifically on the romance genre and is intended for adult readers.\n\n===Tap===\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Tap Original - The Babysitter Part III.jpg|thumb|right|Cover artwork for one of Tap's biggest Original Series, ''The Babysitter''.{{deletable image-caption|Sunday, 17 June 2018|PROD}}]] -->\nOn February 21, 2017, Wattpad launched a chat stories app called ''Tap''.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://techcrunch.com/2017/02/22/wattpad-debuts-tap-an-app-for-reading-chat-style-short-stories/|title = Wattpad debuts Tap, an app for reading chat-style short stories|date = February 22, 2017|accessdate = June 13, 2017|website =TechCrunch |publisher = |last =Perez |first =Sarah }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = https://the-digital-reader.com/2017/02/22/wattpad-launches-chat-style-reading-app-tap/|title = Wattpad Launches Chat-Style Reading App Tap|date = February 22, 2017|accessdate = June 13, 2017|website =The Digital Reader |publisher = |last =Hoffelder |first =Nate }}</ref> ''Tap'' offers stories in the form of text messages as if reading a private conversation on someone else's phone. The app was an early success, with over 240 million taps in the first few weeks after the launch.<ref>{{Cite news|url = https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/books-and-media/wattpad-taps-into-a-new-genre/article34335985/|title = Wattpad taps into a new genre|date = March 17, 2017|accessdate = June 13, 2017|website =The Globe and Mail |publisher =|last =Dingman |first =Shane }}</ref> On July 28, 2017, Tap launched 'Tap Originals', a series of original stories produced by its top-tier writers every single week, with some of those series working on an episode-by-episode basis.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://techcrunch.com/2017/07/28/wattpad-takes-chat-fiction-beyond-text-with-launch-of-tap-originals/|title = Wattpad takes 'chat fiction' beyond text with launch of Tap Originals|date = July 28, 2017|access-date = December 1, 2017|website =Tech Crunch |publisher = |last =Perez |first =Sarah }}</ref> Some of Tap's most successful original series include ''HIDE'', ''The Babysitter'' and ''Charlie, Charlie''.\n\n=== Wattpad Next Beta ===<!-- This information was retrieved from these references. You can edit them if you spot wrong grammars or spellings, or with other reasons, but do not delete them, unless with a valid reason in your summary, otherwise, I will undo your deletion of this sentence. -->\n\nOn November 13, 2018, Wattpad Next Beta was launched<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nextbeta.wattpad.com/|title=Wattpad Next|website=Wattpad Next|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-09}}</ref> to selected countries<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2018/11/13/wattpad-announces-us-launch-for-wattpad-next-beta-program-adding-exclusive-paid-content-to-the-platform|title=Wattpad Announces US Launch for Wattpad Next (Beta) Program, Adding Exclusive Paid Content to the Platform|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-09}}</ref> for early testing such as [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[Mexico]], [[United Kingdom]], and the [[Philippines]]. The launch of the Next Beta has over 50 exclusively selected stories to be paid with WattPad Coins, that can be earned by having your reader spend Wattpad Coins to show them support or by purchasing them with real-world currency to unlock participating Next Beta stories. This has been launched to create a way for writers to earn money through their work and to provide support for readers. WattPad has planned a fast-follow launch for Wattpad Next (Beta) in [[Spanish language|Spanish-speaking regions]] and to expand the program, and was available in [[Latin America]] and [[Spain]], beginning May 27, 2019 and later worldwide on July 11th the same year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/714856760-news-updates-april-3rd-2019-thank-you-next|title=News & Updates - April 3rd, 2019 - Thank you, Next. Introducing Paid Stories. - Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref>\n\nIn an article<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://support.wattpad.com/hc/en-us/articles/360022692911-Introducing-Paid-Stories|title=Introducing Paid Stories|website=Help Center|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref> posted on September 17, 2019, almost a month before the 1st year since the launch of Next Beta, The Wattpad Team has announced the ending of the Next Beta program after results from the program showed that \"Wattpadders are ready for a program that funds writers.\". By that time, it was renamed as \"Paid Stories\".\n\nThere are also paid books which requires an reader to pay money to read further chapters in the book. Usually the paid books are in better quality than the ones that are not paid.\n\n== Usage ==\n===Statistics=== \nAs of August 2019:\n* 85% of its traffic and usage comes from mobile devices,<ref name=\"gigaom.com\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/wattpad-funding-tencent-tv-film-entertainment-1202666935/|title=Wattpad Banks $51 Million From Tencent, Other Investors to Fund Entertainment Projects|author=Mathew Ingram|date=2018-01-17|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* the site has 80 million monthly users,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://betakit.com/wattpad-tracks-80-million-monthly-users-23-percent-growth-since-2018/|title=Wattpad tracks 80 million monthly users, 23 percent increase since 2018|date=2019-08-15|website=BetaKit|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n* there are over 665 million story uploads in total,<ref name=\"Wattpad\"/>\n* 70% of users are female. 80% of whom are millennials or Gen Z.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rao |first1=Sonia |title=How 'The Kissing Booth' went from a teenager's passion project to a Netflix sensation |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/how-the-kissing-booth-went-from-a-teenagers-passion-project-to-a-netflix-sensation/2018/07/13/712c0072-84fe-11e8-9e80-403a221946a7_story.html?noredirect=on |website=Washington Post |publisher=WP Company LLC |accessdate=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== New authors and teens ===\nThe most frequently voted stories appear on the \"What's Hot List\". According to the profiles visible on the site, many of these authors are teenagers.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}{{Primary source inline|date=January 2020}}\n\nWattpad section also has a Featured Story list, which promotes content reviewed and approved by staff and an editorial review board. Many of these featured stories are written by self-published and professional writers from different genres. Famous authors like [[Margaret Atwood]], [[Paulo Coelho]] and [[R L Stine]] have also joined wattpad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/publishedwriters/|title=Promote and Market your Book on Wattpad for Published Authors|last=Wattpad|website=www.wattpad.com}}</ref> Wattpad also encourages the writers to interact with their audience and promote their stories across social media websites like Twitter, Facebook, YouTube and Instagram.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://support.wattpad.com/hc/en-us|title=Help Center|website=support.wattpad.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Contests ===\nWattpad hosts a number of writing contests each year, including the annual Watty Awards, the largest writing competition in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wattpad.com/go/writing-contests/|title=Writing Contests on Wattpad|website=Wattpad}}</ref> In 2011, The Watty Awards introduced three entry levels (Popular, On The Rise, and Undiscovered) to allow greater chances of winning for every type of writer. [[Competition|Contests]] are open to anyone who has a Wattpad account.\n\nDuring the summer of 2012, Wattpad in collaboration with [[Margaret Atwood]], Canadian poet/novelist/literary critic, held the \"Wattys\": the first major poetry contest offering a chance to poets on Wattpad to compete against each other in one of two categories, either as an \"Enthusiast\" or a \"Competitor\". It has been going ever since, and now the contest is open to books of all genres.\n\n=== Publishing ===\nWattpad has formed ties with publishing houses to try to help Wattpad authors to receive compensation for their works. A new branch, Wattpad Studios, was developed to connect popular writers to both the publishing and film industries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/04/26/wattpad-studios/|title=Wattpad sets its sights on brands, publishers and Hollywood with Wattpad Studios|last=Ha|first=Anthony|website=TechCrunch|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref> Wattpad has, in the past, teamed up with publishing groups such as [[Sourcebooks]] to help Wattpad authors receive book deals, and get their work into hard copies.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/childrens/childrens-book-news/article/58997-sourcebooks-wattpad-team-up-to-launch-ya-authors.html|title=Sourcebooks, Wattpad Team Up To Launch YA Authors|newspaper=PublishersWeekly.com|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref> More traditional publishing houses such as [[Random House]] and [[HarperCollins]] have approached popular Wattpad writers to negotiate publishing deals, allowing the website to serve as a springboard into the more traditional publishing industry.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/what-wattpad-youtube-stories-transforming-book-publishing-1710151|title=What Is Wattpad? The 'YouTube For Stories' Is Transforming Book Publishing|date=2014-10-23|newspaper=International Business Times|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref>\n\nAuthor [[Anna Todd]], whose work ''After'' has received over a billion reads on the site, was given a publishing deal with [[Simon & Schuster]] to turn her online work into a multiple-book published saga. A film version starring Josephine Langford, Hero Fiennes Tiffin, Selma Blair, Jennifer Beals, Peter Gallagher, and Shane Paul McGhie was released by Aviron Pictures on April 12, 2019.\n\n==== Wattpad Books ====\nOn January 24, 2019, Wattpad launched publishing division Wattpad Books led by Wattpad Studios' Publishing Deputy Manager Ashleigh Gardner, with operations managed by Wattpad Studios' Publishing Director Deanna McFadden.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/1/23/wattpad-launches-wattpad-books-a-new-publishing-division-to-bring-diverse-data-backed-stories-to-book-lovers-everywhere|title=Wattpad Launches Wattpad Books, a New Publishing Division to Bring Diverse, Data-Backed Stories to Book-Lovers Everywhere|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref> According to CEO Allen Lau, this project was in an effort to take the \"guesswork\" out of publishing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.utoronto.ca/news/wattpad-founded-u-t-alumni-launches-publishing-division-new-york-times|title=Wattpad, founded by U of T alumni, launches publishing division: New York Times|website=University of Toronto News|language=en|access-date=2019-03-24}}</ref>\n\nWattpad Books acquisitions uses a mix of their Story DNA Machine Learning technology (algorithms) learning with human editors.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/1/24/18195753/wattpad-books-launching-publishing-imprint-self|title=Wattpad is launching a publishing imprint called Wattpad Books|last=Liptak|first=Andrew|date=2019-01-24|website=The Verge|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref> This human-and-digital acquisitions team look to Wattpad's large and existing digital library (over half a billion titles) in order to select notable material for publication.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/lilyrugo/2019/01/30/wattpads-new-book-publishing-branch-uses-machine-deep-learning-to-find-stories/|title=Wattpad's New Book Publishing Branch Uses Machine Deep Learning To Find Stories|last=Rugo|first=Lily|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-03-24}}</ref> According to Wattpad Books leader Ashleigh Gardner, this is in an effort to combat bias inherent in human editors.<ref name=\":2\" /> Gardner says that this technology analyzes the data behind each title, looking at story structure and word use in addition to levels of reader engagement per title.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebookseller.com/futurebook/algorithms-trends-and-partnerships-inside-story-wattpad-books-942486|title=Algorithms, trends and partnerships: the inside story of Wattpad books|last=Flatt|first=Molly|date=February 4, 2019|website=The Bookseller|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref> This data is then compared to analyses of other books on Wattpad and in the public domain.<ref name=\":0\" /> Once all the data has been collected and engagement has been looked at, human staffers read the titles and create their list.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nAll published titles are an amalgamation of international hits and notable but known material from their digital library.<ref name=\":1\" /> These titles are distributed by Macmillan in the United States of America, Raincoast Books in Canada, and Penguin Random House in India and the United Kingdom, with their Fall 2019 list available in leading North American retailers.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/7/8/penguin-random-house-india-partners-with-wattpad-to-showcase-exclusive-content-and-innovative-promotions|title=Penguin Random House India Partners with Wattpad to Showcase Exclusive Content and Innovative Promotions|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/8/8/penguin-random-house-uk-collaborates-with-wattpad-books-to-bring-global-wattpad-hits-to-readers-in-the-uk|title=Penguin Random House UK collaborates with Wattpad Books to bring global Wattpad hits to readers in the UK|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref> Outside North America, Gardner has sold the rights to Hachette (France) for Deanna Cameron\u2019s ''What Happened Last Night.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://publishingperspectives.com/2019/01/wattpad-books-new-publishing-division-opened-canada/|title=Wattpad Launches a Book Publishing Division Called Wattpad Books|date=2019-01-24|website=Publishing Perspectives|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref> Additionally, Lauren Palphreyman's rights to ''Cupid's Match'' have been sold in French (Hachette) and German (S. Fischer Verlgage).<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://social.techcrunch.com/2019/01/24/online-storytelling-community-wattpad-launches-its-own-publishing-arm-wattpad-books/|title=Online storytelling community Wattpad launches its own publishing arm, Wattpad Books|website=TechCrunch|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref>\n\nWattpad's first list consists of six young adult novels.<ref name=\":3\" /> ''The QB Bad Boy & Me'' by Tay Marley (28.8 million reads) will be their lead title and was slated for release on August 13, 2019.<ref name=\":3\" /> The remaining five books will be released between September and October 2019 and include: ''Trapeze'' by Leigh Ansell (2.5 million reads), ''What Happened That Night'' by Deanna Cameron (over 1 million reads), ''Saving Everest'' by Sky Reads (17.2 million reads), ''Cupid's Match'' by Lauren Palphreyman (46.4 million reads), and ''I'm a Gay Wizard'' by V.S. Santoni (404,000 reads).<ref name=\":3\" /> Wattpad hopes to publish 18 titles in their 2020 list.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nBesides Wattpad Books, Wattpad announced partnership with Anvil Publishing, Inc., one of Philippines' leading publishers, to create Bliss Books, a YA imprint with Filipino Young Adult and romance fanatics as their target market.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/4/15/anvil-publishing-and-wattpad-team-up-for-bliss-books-a-new-ya-imprint-for-the-philippines|title=Anvil Publishing and Wattpad Team Up for Bliss Books, a New YA Imprint for the Philippines|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref>\n\n=== Entertainment ===\n[[Netflix]] film [[The Kissing Booth]] was written in 2011 by author Beth Reekles. It originated as a story on Wattpad where it won a Watty Award for \"Most Popular Teen Fiction\" in Wattpad's annual writing contest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2013/04/beth-reekles-kissing-booth/316454/|title=Meet the 17-Year-Old Who's Already Got a Three-Book Deal with Random House|first=Jen|last=Doll|date=Apr 9, 2013|website=The Atlantic|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref> By 2012 it had amassed over 19 million reads on Wattpad and, in 2013, was published by [[Penguin Random House]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://social.techcrunch.com/2018/06/14/netflixs-latest-hit-the-kissing-booth-is-a-wattpad-success-story/|title=Netflix's latest hit 'The Kissing Booth' is a Wattpad success story|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref> In an interview with [[Forbes]], Reekles explains what drew her to Wattpad: \"I loved the feeling of community on the site, and when I began to share, I liked the anonymity of it because I was so self-conscious about my writing and hadn't shared it with anyone before.\"<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/adamrowe1/2018/06/26/why-beth-reekles-is-the-wattpad-success-story-behind-netflix-hit-the-kissing-booth/|title=Why Beth Reekles Is The Wattpad Success Story Behind Netflix Hit 'The Kissing Booth'|first=Adam|last=Rowe|website=Forbes|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\nSince [[The Kissing Booth]] premiered on [[Netflix]] on May 11, 2018, [[Ted Sarandos]] called it \"one of the most-watched movies in the country, and maybe in the world\".<ref name=\"auto1\"/> The Kissing Booth was the fourth most-popular movie in [[IMDb]]'s popularity rankings in June 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/netflix-says-the-kissing-booth-is-one-of-the-most-watched-movies-in-the-country-2018-6|title=Netflix says its teen romcom 'The Kissing Booth' is 'one of the most-watched movies in the country'|first=Travis|last=Clark|website=Business Insider|accessdate=Jun 2, 2019|date=2018-06-12}}</ref> Wattpad has also inked deals with Asian distribution partners,such as pan-Asian streaming platform [[Iflix]] to co-produce dozens of original movies based on Wattpad stories out of Indonesia,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/wattpad-strikes-original-content-partnership-with-asian-digital-platform-iflix-1202445743/|title=Wattpad Strikes Original Content Partnership With Asian Digital Platform Iflix|last=|first=|date=2018-08-15|website=Deadline|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and Singapore's [[Mediacorp]], to bring Wattpad stories to Mediacorp's FTA channels such as [[Channel 5 (Singapore)|Channel 5]] (with exception of [[CNA (news channel)|CNA]]) and its streaming service Toggle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://company.wattpad.com/blog/2019/4/23/wattpad-and-mediacorp-partner-to-bring-singapore-stories-from-written-word-to-national-screens|title=Wattpad and Mediacorp partner to bring Singapore stories from written word to national screens|website=Wattpad HQ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-14}}</ref>\n\nWattpad, with [[AwesomenessTV]],  produces [[Hulu]]'s popular [[Light as a Feather (TV series)|Light as a Feather]].\n\n== Effects on Writers  ==\nOnline writing communities like Wattpad help adolescent writers learn and grow their craft from constructive feedback and criticism, according to a recent study.<ref name=\":02\">{{Cite journal|last=Birch|first=Heather|date=2016|title=Feedback in Online Writing Forums: Effects on Adolescent Writers|url=https://scholarworks.wmich.edu/wte/vol5/iss1/5/|journal=Teaching/Writing: The Journal of Writing Teacher Education|volume=5|pages=Article 5|via=}}</ref> Composed of students and their experiences on online writing platforms, the study aims to show how constructive criticism affects their writing process. Most participants prefer serious feedback over subtle critiquing, based on the results.<ref name=\":02\" />\n\nWattpad as well as similar online writing communities help young authors build and construct their self perception as writers, as well as establishes an audience and interact with readers.<ref name=\":12\">{{Cite journal|last=Ramdarshan Bold|first=Melanie|date=2016|title=The Return of the Social Author: Negotiating Authority and Influence on Wattpad|journal=Convergence|volume=|pages=|doi=10.1177/1354856516654459}}</ref> It acts as a gateway into the publishing realm and offers hands-on experience with digital writing. This type of experience helps writers develop personal authorship.<ref name=\":12\" />\n\nWattpad offers unique features that other writing platforms do not, like the interactive margin commenting. Readers can add comments and feedback by individual lines and paragraphs as they are reading rather than after the chapter or story is finished.<ref name=\":22\">{{Cite journal|last=Rebora|first=Simone|date=2018|title=A New Research Programme for Reading Research: Analysing Comments in the Margins on Wattpad|url=https://digitcult.lim.di.unimi.it/index.php/dc/article/view/67|journal=DigitCult - Scientific Journal on Digital Cultures|volume=3|pages=19\u201336|via=}}</ref> These comment sections are available to all users and readers for reacting to the chapter, offering constructive feedback, or just for personal input, allowing readers to see what others are thinking and writers to see how readers are responding.<ref name=\":22\" />\n\n== Copyright issues ==\nEarly in its history, some of the large volumes of user-uploaded material hosted on Wattpad was [[copyright infringement|copyrighted material]] created by authors who did not grant republication rights. In May 2009, an article in 'The New York Times' noted, \"''Sites like [[Scribd]] and Wattpad, which invite users to upload documents like college theses and self-published novels, have been the target of industry grumbling in recent weeks, as illegal reproductions of popular titles have turned up on them''\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/05/12/technology/internet/12digital.html|title=With E-Readers Comes Wider Piracy of Books|last=Rich|first=Motoko|date=2009-05-11|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\nThe Wattpad website notes, \"We do not welcome upload of material that violate its copyright terms,\" but also states \"it is simply not possible to screen and verify all posted content.\"<ref name=\"writerprogram\">{{citation|url=http://www.wattpad.com/writerprogram|title=Wattpad \u2013 Writer Program}}.</ref> In response to industry criticism, in April 2009 (before the publication of the ''New York Times'' article that named Wattpad as a vehicle for user-generated e-book infringement) Wattpad announced an \"Authors In Charge\" program, designed to allow authors or their representatives to identify and directly remove infringing content from the site, but this program is designed specifically for \"authors with published books for sale.\"<ref name=writerprogram/> Authors may begin their stories on Wattpad and then chose to publish their work. In most cases, the work on Wattpad is only a sample to insure funds going to them in regards to their writing.\n\n== Competitors and similar sites==\n[[Bookmate]] and the long-established and popular sites [[FanFiction.Net]] and [[Fiction Press]] (a spin-off site for original fiction) also serve as hubs for online prose. An alternative site which is free and open source is [[Archive of Our Own]], or AO3.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gizmodo.com/how-to-find-the-best-fanfiction-on-the-internet-1723984681|title=How To Find The Best Fanfiction On the Internet|last=Hale-Stern|first=Kaila|work=Gizmodo|access-date=2017-12-06|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{E-book digital distribution platforms}}\n{{Self-publishing}}\n\n[[Category:Wattpad]]\n[[Category:Canadian publishers (people)]]\n[[Category:E-book suppliers]]\n[[Category:Electronic paper technology]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) software]]\n[[Category:BlackBerry software]]\n[[Category:IOS software]]\n[[Category:E-book sources]]\n[[Category:Online publishing companies]]\n[[Category:Self-publishing companies]]\n[[Category:Universal Windows Platform apps]]\n", "name_user": "ZappaOMatic", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEffects on Writers:Not a proper noun", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wattpad"}
{"title_page": "Saini", "text_new": "{{short description|Caste of North India}}\n{{About|the Saini (Mali) community of Punjab, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir, Chandigarh and Delhi|the Mali community who were not recorded as Saini prior to  1937 |Mali caste|and|Rajput Mali|the Bhagrathi or Gola community of Western Uttar Pradesh|Bhagirathi Mali}}\n{{distinguish|Siani (disambiguation){{!}}Siani|Sinai (disambiguation){{!}}Sinai}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{pp|small=yes}} \n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2014}}\n{{Infobox caste\n|caste_name= Saini\n|populated_states= [[Punjab, India]], [[Haryana]], [[Himachal Pradesh]], [[Jammu & Kashmir]], [[Chandigarh]] and [[Delhi]]\n|country= Primarily India\n}}\n\n'''Saini''' ({{Audio|saini.ogg|pronunciation}}) is a [[caste]] of [[North India]] who were traditionally landowners ([[zamindars]]) and farmers. Sainis claim to be descendants of a king, [[Shurasena]], as well as of [[Krishna]] and [[King Porus|Porus]], and to be related to the ancient Shoorsaini clan,<ref name = \"Shoorsaini\">'' \"The Sainis believe that their ancestors were Yadavas and that it was the same lineage in which Krishna was born. In the 43rd generation of the Yadavas there was a king known as Shoor or Sur, the son of King Vidaratha....It was in the name of these, father and son, that the community was known as Shoorsaini or Sursaini.\"'' People of India: Haryana, p 430, Kumar Suresh Singh, Madan Lal Sharma, A. K. Bhatia, Anthropological Survey of India, Published by Published on behalf of Anthropological Survey of India by Manohar Publishers, 1994</ref> noted in [[Puranic]] literature. Saini community is given representation in government jobs and education institutes under [[Other Backward Class]] (OBC)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chdengineering.gov.in/pages/list_obc.pdf|title=CENTRAL LIST OF OTHER BACKWARD CLASSES|last=|first=|date=|website=CHANDIGARH ENGINEERING DEPARTMENT|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> category in states of [[Uttar Pradesh]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/opinion/17-most-backward-castes-may-play-kingmaker-as-purvanchal-gears-up-to-vote-in-final-phase-2141707.html|title=17 Most Backward Castes May Play Kingmaker as Purvanchal Gears Up to Vote in Final Phase|website=News18|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>, [[Punjab (India)|Punjab]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/saini-swarnkarsunar-communities-to-be-backward-classes-in-punjab-3024245/|title=Saini, Swarnkar/Sunar communities to be backward classes in Punjab|date=10 September 2016|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>, [[Haryana]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/haryana-government-adds-kushwaha-keori-maurya-castes-to-bc-list/articleshow/25267747.cms?from=mdr|title=Haryana government adds Kushwaha, Keori, Maurya castes to BC list|date=5 November 2013|work=The Economic Times|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>, [[Rajasthan]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/rajasthan-assembly-polls-2018-rss-stronghold-anta-has-been-electing-influential-leaders/story-1PBDYFzDd0luazjapjzpfK.html|title=Rajasthan assembly polls 2018: RSS stronghold, Anta, has been electing influential leaders|date=11 September 2018|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/congress-rift-in-rajasthan-shows-but-sachin-pilot-on-course-for-win/cid/1677830|title=Cong rift shows but Sachin Pilot on course for win|website=The Telegraph|language=en|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref> and [[Madhya Pradesh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bhopal/Commission-starts-hearing-on-inclusion-of-OBCs-from-Madhya-Pradesh/articleshow/42244508.cms|title=Shubha Mudgal: Commission starts hearing on inclusion of OBCs from Madhya Pradesh|last=N|first=TN|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref> The 1901 census noted that people using the Shoorsaini name were by then found only in Punjab, Haryana, [[Jammu and Kashmir]], [[Himachal Pradesh]] and [[Delhi]]. Sainis also claim themselves to be [[Rajput Mali|Mali Rajput]]s.<ref name = \"Saini Rajput\"/>\n\nAs both a statutory agricultural tribe and a designated [[martial race]] during the [[British Raj]] era that followed the [[Indian Rebellion of 1857]], Sainis had been chiefly engaged in both agriculture and military service since then until recent times. However, since the independence of India, Sainis have diversified into different trades and professions other than military and agriculture. Sainis are now also seen in increasing numbers as businessmen, lawyers, professors, civil servants, engineers, doctors and research scientists, etc.<ref>''\"The members of Saini community are employed in business and white-collar jobs and as teachers, administrators, lawyers, doctors and defence personnel.\"'' People of India, National Series Volume VI, India's Communities N-Z, p 3091, KS Singh, Anthropological Survey of India, Oxford University Press, 1998</ref>\n\nSainis profess in both Hinduism and Sikhism. They have a national organisation called ''Saini Rajput Mahasabha'' located in Delhi, established in 1920.<ref name = \"Saini Rajput Mahasabha\">People of India: Haryana, p 437, Kumar Suresh Singh, Madan Lal Sharma, A. K. Bhatia, Anthropological Survey of India, Published by Published on behalf of Anthropological Survey of India by Manohar Publishers, 1994</ref>\n\n==History==\n===Mythology===\n\nThe Sainis of Jalandhar and Hoshiarpur districts claim to be the descendants of the Rajputs of the Yaduvanshi or Surasena lineage who ruled these kingdoms, who came to these areas to avoid forced conversion to Islam.<ref name = \"Surasena Mathura\">\"Surasena refers to an ancient region named after a Jadu raja who is believed to have lived before Krishna. Bayana (near Mathura) from where the Jadus ruled ...\" ''Against History, Against State: Counterperspectives from the Margins'', p 54, Shail Mayaram, published by Permanent Black, 2004</ref>\n\n===Academic===\nGahlot and Banshidhar (1989) indicate some commonality in origin with Rajput Malis of Rajputana who are also stated to be of Rajput descent but these scholars add that out of the two the Sainis continued to maintain their Rajput character despite adoption of agriculture in the era of Muslim ascendancy.<ref name = \"Saini Rajput\">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DuAtAAAAMAAJ |quote=In the Punjab in the sub-mountainous region the community came to be known as 'Saini'. It maintained its Rajput character despite migration. In other parts, it came to be called by the name of \"Kshatriya-Mali\" (Rajput Mali) |title=Castes and Tribes of Rajasthan |page=108 |first1=Sukhvir Singh |last1=Gahlot |first2=Banshi |last2=Dhar |publisher=Jain Brothers |year=1989}}</ref> The former were also included as part of Rajputs in Marwar State Census of 1891<ref name=\"Marwar Rajput sub-category\">\"One sub-category recognized among Rajputs is that of the minor agricultural castes which comprises among others, Sirvis, Mali and Kallu or Patel.\" ''The Castes of Marwar, Being Census Report of 1891'', p vi, Hardyal Singh, Edition: 2, published by Books Treasure, Original from the University of Michigan</ref>\n\n===British era===\n\nDuring the British period Sainis were classified as both a statutory agricultural tribe and, later, a martial race.<ref name=\"Mazumder2003\">{{cite book|first=Rajit K. |last=Mazumder|title=The Indian army and the making of Punjab|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O4Wop9vwS9sC&pg=PA105 |year=2003|publisher=Orient Blackswan|isbn=978-81-7824-059-6|pages=99, 105, 205}}</ref> The latter was an administrative device based on the now-discredited theories of [[scientific racism]]: ethnic communities were categorised as being either martial or non-martial, with the latter being those who were thought to be unfit to serve in armies due to their sedentary lifestyles.<ref name=rand>{{Cite journal|last=Rand|first=Gavin|title=Martial Races and Imperial Subjects: Violence and Governance in Colonial India 1857\u20131914|journal= European Review of History|volume=13|issue=1|pages=1\u201320|publisher=Routledge|date=March 2006|url=|doi=10.1080/13507480600586726}}</ref><ref name=\"Street\">{{cite book |title=Martial Races: The military, race and masculinity in British Imperial Culture, 1857-1914 |last=Streets |first=Heather |year=2004 |publisher=Manchester University Press |isbn=978-0-7190-6962-8 |page=241 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BscnZT_1po8C}}</ref> The community was also one of several peasant peoples who benefitted from the development of the [[Punjab Canal Colonies]], through which they obtained land grants from the British authorities, especially in the [[Chenab Colony]] following the introduction of the [[Punjab Land Alienation Act, 1900]].<ref>{{cite book |title=The Punjab Under Imperialism, 1885-1947 |first=Imran |last=Ali |publisher=Princeton University Press |year=2014 |origyear=1988 |isbn=978-1-40085-958-0 |pages=51, 56, 64, 73 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MgUABAAAQBAJ&pg=PA51}}</ref>\n\nSome Saini landlords were also appointed as ''[[zaildar]]s'', or revenue-collectors, in various districts.<ref name = \"Hissar Zaildar\">History of Hisar: From Inception to Independence, 1935\u20131947, p 312, M. M. Juneja, Published by Modern Book Co., 1989</ref>\n\n==Marriage==\nTraditionally, Sainis have been married through Vedic ceremonies performed by Brahmins of [[Sanatani]] tradition. However, [[Sikh]] Sainis marry by [[Anand Karaj]] ritual.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/up-mla-aditi-singh-to-marry-punjab-congress-lawmaker-angad-singh-saini/articleshow/72090892.cms|title=UP MLA Aditi Singh to marry Punjab Congress lawmaker Angad Singh Saini|last=Singh|first=IP|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[Anthropological Survey of India]], \"The Saini are endogamous community and observe exogamy at village and gotra level.\" Remarriage after the death of a spouse is permitted nowadays, as is divorce.<ref>People of India, National Series Volume VI, India's Communities N-Z, p 3090, KS Singh, Anthropological Survey of India, Oxford University Press, 1998</ref>\n\n==Notable people==\n{{main article|List of Saini people}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Surasena Kingdom]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth = 30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.SainiOnline.com SainiOnline.com]\n*[http://www.sainiinfo.com SainiInfo.com]\n\n{{Ethnic groups, tribes and clans of the Punjab}}\n{{Rajput Groups of India}}\n\n[[Category:Saini| ]]\n[[Category:Indian castes]]\n[[Category:Indian family names]]\n[[Category:Punjabi tribes]]\n[[Category:Hindu communities]]\n[[Category:Social groups of Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:Social groups of Haryana]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Caste of North India}}\n{{About|the Saini (Mali) community of Punjab, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir, Chandigarh and Delhi|the Mali community who were not recorded as Saini prior to  1937 |Mali caste|and|Rajput Mali|the Bhagrathi or Gola community of Western Uttar Pradesh|Bhagirathi Mali}}\n{{distinguish|Siani (disambiguation){{!}}Siani|Sinai (disambiguation){{!}}Sinai}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{pp|small=yes}} \n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2014}}\n{{Infobox caste\n|caste_name= Saini\n|populated_states= [[Punjab, India]], [[Haryana]], [[Himachal Pradesh]], [[Jammu & Kashmir]], [[Chandigarh]] and [[Delhi]]\n|country= Primarily India\n}}\n\n'''Saini''' ({{Audio|saini.ogg|pronunciation}}) is a [[caste]] of [[North India]] who were traditionally landowners ([[zamindars]]) and farmers. Sainis claim to be descendants of a king, [[Shurasena]], as well as of [[Krishna]] and [[King Porus|Porus]], and to be related to the ancient Shoorsaini clan,<ref name = \"Shoorsaini\">'' \"The Sainis believe that their ancestors were Yadavas and that it was the same lineage in which Krishna was born. In the 43rd generation of the Yadavas there was a king known as Shoor or Sur, the son of King Vidaratha....It was in the name of these, father and son, that the community was known as Shoorsaini or Sursaini.\"'' People of India: Haryana, p 430, Kumar Suresh Singh, Madan Lal Sharma, A. K. Bhatia, Anthropological Survey of India, Published by Published on behalf of Anthropological Survey of India by Manohar Publishers, 1994</ref> noted in [[Puranic]] literature. Saini community is given representation in government jobs and education institutes under [[Other Backward Class]] (OBC)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chdengineering.gov.in/pages/list_obc.pdf|title=CENTRAL LIST OF OTHER BACKWARD CLASSES|last=|first=|date=|website=CHANDIGARH ENGINEERING DEPARTMENT|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> category in states of [[Uttar Pradesh]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/opinion/17-most-backward-castes-may-play-kingmaker-as-purvanchal-gears-up-to-vote-in-final-phase-2141707.html|title=17 Most Backward Castes May Play Kingmaker as Purvanchal Gears Up to Vote in Final Phase|website=News18|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>, [[Punjab (India)|Punjab]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/saini-swarnkarsunar-communities-to-be-backward-classes-in-punjab-3024245/|title=Saini, Swarnkar/Sunar communities to be backward classes in Punjab|date=10 September 2016|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>, [[Haryana]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/haryana-government-adds-kushwaha-keori-maurya-castes-to-bc-list/articleshow/25267747.cms?from=mdr|title=Haryana government adds Kushwaha, Keori, Maurya castes to BC list|date=5 November 2013|work=The Economic Times|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>, [[Rajasthan]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/rajasthan-assembly-polls-2018-rss-stronghold-anta-has-been-electing-influential-leaders/story-1PBDYFzDd0luazjapjzpfK.html|title=Rajasthan assembly polls 2018: RSS stronghold, Anta, has been electing influential leaders|date=11 September 2018|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/congress-rift-in-rajasthan-shows-but-sachin-pilot-on-course-for-win/cid/1677830|title=Cong rift shows but Sachin Pilot on course for win|website=The Telegraph|language=en|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref> and [[Madhya Pradesh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bhopal/Commission-starts-hearing-on-inclusion-of-OBCs-from-Madhya-Pradesh/articleshow/42244508.cms|title=Shubha Mudgal: Commission starts hearing on inclusion of OBCs from Madhya Pradesh|last=N|first=TN|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref> The 1901 census noted that people using the Shoorsaini name were by then found only in Punjab, Haryana, [[Jammu and Kashmir]], [[Himachal Pradesh]] and [[Delhi]]. Sainis also claim themselves to be [[Rajput Mali|Mali Rajput]]s.<ref name = \"Saini Rajput\"/>\n\nAs both a statutory agricultural tribe and a designated [[martial race]] during the [[British Raj]] era that followed the [[Indian Rebellion of 1857]], Sainis had been chiefly engaged in both agriculture and military service since then until recent times. However, since the independence of India, Sainis have diversified into different trades and professions other than military and agriculture. Sainis are now also seen in increasing numbers as businessmen, lawyers, professors, civil servants, engineers, doctors and research scientists, etc.<ref>''\"The members of Saini community are employed in business and white-collar jobs and as teachers, administrators, lawyers, doctors and defence personnel.\"'' People of India, National Series Volume VI, India's Communities N-Z, p 3091, KS Singh, Anthropological Survey of India, Oxford University Press, 1998</ref>\n\nSainis profess in both Hinduism and Sikhism. They have a national organisation called ''Saini Rajput Mahasabha'' located in Delhi, established in 1920.<ref name = \"Saini Rajput Mahasabha\">People of India: Haryana, p 437, Kumar Suresh Singh, Madan Lal Sharma, A. K. Bhatia, Anthropological Survey of India, Published by Published on behalf of Anthropological Survey of India by Manohar Publishers, 1994</ref>\n\n==History==\n===Mythology===\n\nThe Sainis of Jalandhar and Hoshiarpur districts claim to be the descendants of the Rajputs of the Yaduvanshi or Surasena lineage who ruled these kingdoms, who came to these areas to avoid forced conversion to Islam.<ref name = \"Surasena Mathura\">\"Surasena refers to an ancient region named after a Jadu raja who is believed to have lived before Krishna. Bayana (near Mathura) from where the Jadus ruled ...\" ''Against History, Against State: Counterperspectives from the Margins'', p 54, Shail Mayaram, published by Permanent Black, 2004</ref>\n\n===Academic===\nGahlot and Banshidhar (1989) indicate some commonality in origin with Rajput Malis of Rajputana who are also stated to be of Rajput descent but these scholars add that out of the two the Sainis continued to maintain their Rajput character despite adoption of agriculture in the era of Muslim ascendancy.<ref name = \"Saini Rajput\">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DuAtAAAAMAAJ |quote=In the Punjab in the sub-mountainous region the community came to be known as 'Saini'. It maintained its Rajput character despite migration. In other parts, it came to be called by the name of \"Kshatriya-Mali\" (Rajput Mail) |title=Castes and Tribes of Rajasthan |page=108 |first1=Sukhvir Singh |last1=Gahlot |first2=Banshi |last2=Dhar |publisher=Jain Brothers |year=1989}}</ref> The former were also included as part of Rajputs in Marwar State Census of 1891<ref name=\"Marwar Rajput sub-category\">\"One sub-category recognized among Rajputs is that of the minor agricultural castes which comprises among others, Sirvis, Mali and Kallu or Patel.\" ''The Castes of Marwar, Being Census Report of 1891'', p vi, Hardyal Singh, Edition: 2, published by Books Treasure, Original from the University of Michigan</ref>\n\n===British era===\n\nDuring the British period Sainis were classified as both a statutory agricultural tribe and, later, a martial race.<ref name=\"Mazumder2003\">{{cite book|first=Rajit K. |last=Mazumder|title=The Indian army and the making of Punjab|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O4Wop9vwS9sC&pg=PA105 |year=2003|publisher=Orient Blackswan|isbn=978-81-7824-059-6|pages=99, 105, 205}}</ref> The latter was an administrative device based on the now-discredited theories of [[scientific racism]]: ethnic communities were categorised as being either martial or non-martial, with the latter being those who were thought to be unfit to serve in armies due to their sedentary lifestyles.<ref name=rand>{{Cite journal|last=Rand|first=Gavin|title=Martial Races and Imperial Subjects: Violence and Governance in Colonial India 1857\u20131914|journal= European Review of History|volume=13|issue=1|pages=1\u201320|publisher=Routledge|date=March 2006|url=|doi=10.1080/13507480600586726}}</ref><ref name=\"Street\">{{cite book |title=Martial Races: The military, race and masculinity in British Imperial Culture, 1857-1914 |last=Streets |first=Heather |year=2004 |publisher=Manchester University Press |isbn=978-0-7190-6962-8 |page=241 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BscnZT_1po8C}}</ref> The community was also one of several peasant peoples who benefitted from the development of the [[Punjab Canal Colonies]], through which they obtained land grants from the British authorities, especially in the [[Chenab Colony]] following the introduction of the [[Punjab Land Alienation Act, 1900]].<ref>{{cite book |title=The Punjab Under Imperialism, 1885-1947 |first=Imran |last=Ali |publisher=Princeton University Press |year=2014 |origyear=1988 |isbn=978-1-40085-958-0 |pages=51, 56, 64, 73 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MgUABAAAQBAJ&pg=PA51}}</ref>\n\nSome Saini landlords were also appointed as ''[[zaildar]]s'', or revenue-collectors, in various districts.<ref name = \"Hissar Zaildar\">History of Hisar: From Inception to Independence, 1935\u20131947, p 312, M. M. Juneja, Published by Modern Book Co., 1989</ref>\n\n==Marriage==\nTraditionally, Sainis have been married through Vedic ceremonies performed by Brahmins of [[Sanatani]] tradition. However, [[Sikh]] Sainis marry by [[Anand Karaj]] ritual.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/up-mla-aditi-singh-to-marry-punjab-congress-lawmaker-angad-singh-saini/articleshow/72090892.cms|title=UP MLA Aditi Singh to marry Punjab Congress lawmaker Angad Singh Saini|last=Singh|first=IP|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[Anthropological Survey of India]], \"The Saini are endogamous community and observe exogamy at village and gotra level.\" Remarriage after the death of a spouse is permitted nowadays, as is divorce.<ref>People of India, National Series Volume VI, India's Communities N-Z, p 3090, KS Singh, Anthropological Survey of India, Oxford University Press, 1998</ref>\n\n==Notable people==\n{{main article|List of Saini people}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Surasena Kingdom]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth = 30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.SainiOnline.com SainiOnline.com]\n*[http://www.sainiinfo.com SainiInfo.com]\n\n{{Ethnic groups, tribes and clans of the Punjab}}\n{{Rajput Groups of India}}\n\n[[Category:Saini| ]]\n[[Category:Indian castes]]\n[[Category:Indian family names]]\n[[Category:Punjabi tribes]]\n[[Category:Hindu communities]]\n[[Category:Social groups of Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:Social groups of Haryana]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "name_user": "Paine Ellsworth", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAcademic:sp.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saini"}
